<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5056694>
    dc:description "Figs. 2, 3. Parabuthus muelleri Prendini, 2000, male (AMNH [AH 3991]), habitus. 2. Dorsal aspect." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5056694/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5056696>
    dc:description "Figs. 4–6. Parabuthus muelleri Prendini, 2000, male (AMNH [AH 3991]), diagnostic characters. 4. Carapace. 5. Dorsal aspect of segments I and II, showing dorsomedian stridulatory region and subtriangular V­shape curvature at posterodorsal edge. 6. Lateral aspect of segments IV, V and telson. Scale bars = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5056696/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5056700>
    dc:description "Figs. 7–9. Parabuthus muelleri Prendini, 2000, male (AMNH [AH 3991]), distribution of trichobothria and macrosetae on the dextral pedipalpal chela. 7. Dorsal aspect. 8. Ventral aspect. 9. Internal aspect. Scale bar = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5056700/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5056704>
    dc:description "Fig. 13. Parabuthus muelleri Prendini, 2000, male (AMNH [AH 3991]), hemispermatophore, ental aspect. Scale bar = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5056704/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5056706>
    dc:description "Fig. 14. The known distribution of Parabuthus muelleri Prendini, 2000 (-), which is endemic to Namibia. Contour interval = 600 m." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5056706/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

